: C ⥤ Type w`, an object `X : C` and `x : F.obj X`,\nthis is the functor `Over X ⥤ Type w` which sends an object of `Over X`\ncorresponding to a morphism `f : Y ⟶ X` to the subtype of `F.obj Y`\nconsisting of those elements `y : F.obj Y` such that `F.map f y = x`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/TypeValuedFlat.html#CategoryTheory.FunctorToTypes.fromOverFunctor","kind":"def","line":77,"name":"CategoryTheory.FunctorToTypes.fromOverFunctor","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/TypeValuedFlat.lean#L77-L81"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/TypeValuedFlat.html#CategoryTheory.FunctorToTypes.mem_fromOverSubfunctor_iff\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">FunctorToTypes</span>.<span class=\"name\">mem_fromOverSubfunctor_iff</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v, u}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor\">Functor</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span> <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">(Type</a> w)</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <span class=\"fn\">C</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><spa